  Membrane systems are biologically motivated theoretical models of distributed and parallel computing. In this paper, we present a membrane algorithm to solve multidimensional 0–1 knapsack problem in linear time by recognizer P systems with input and with active membranes using 2-division. This algorithm can also be modified to solve general 0–1 integer programming problem. Keywords Membrane computing ; P System ; NP -complete problem ; Multidimensional 0–1 knapsack problem ; 0–1 Integer programming problem [1] A. Alhazov, C. Martín-Vide, L. Pan Solving a PSPACE -complete problem by P systems with restricted active membranes Fund. Inform., 58 (2) (2003), pp. 66–77 [2] M.R. Garey, D.J. Johnson, Computers and Intractability. A Guide to the Theory of NP-Completeness, W.H. Freeman, San Francisco, 1979. [3] B. Gavish, H. Pirkul Allocation of data bases and processors in a distributed computing system Manage. Distrib. Data Process., 31 (1982), pp. 215–231 [4] Gh. Păun, Computing with membranes, J. Comput. System Sci. 61(1) (2000) 108–143, and TUCS Research Report 208, 1998 ( http://www.tucs.fi ). [5] Gh. Păun P systems with active membranes: attacking NP-complete problems J. Automata, Lang. Combin., 6 (1) (2001), pp. 75–90 [6] G.h. Păun Membrane Computing: An Introduction Springer, Heidelberg (2002) [7] M.J. Pérez-Jiménez, A. Riscos Núñez, A linear-time solution to the knapsack problem using active membranes, In: A. Alhazov, C. Martín-Vide, Gh. Păun (Eds.), Preproceedings of the Workshop on Membrane Computing. Tarragona, Spain, July 17–22, 2003. [8] M.J. Pérez-Jiménez, A. Romero-Jiménez, F. Sancho-Caparrini Teoría de la Complejidad en Modelos de Computatión Celular con Membranas Editorial Kronos, Sevilla (2002) [9] M.J. Pérez-Jiménez, A. Romero Jiménez, F. Sancho-Caparrini Complexity classes in models of cellular computing with membranes Natural Comput., 2 (3) (2003), pp. 265–285 [10] M.J. Pérez-Jiménez, A. Romero Jiménez, F. Sancho-Caparrini, A polynomial complexity class in P systems using membrane division, The Fifth Workshop on Descriptional Complexity of Formal Systems, Budapest, Hunagary, July 12–14, 2003. [11] M.J. Pérez-Jiménez, A. Romero Jiménez, F. Sancho Caparrini, Solving validity problem by active membranes with input, In: M. Cavaliere, C. Martín-Vide, Gh. Păun, (Eds.), Proceedings of the Brainstorming Week on Membrane Computing, Report GRLMC 26/03, 2003, 270–278. [12] W. Shih A branch & bound method for the multiconstraint zero-one knapsack problem J. Oper. Res. Soc., 30 (1979), pp. 369–378 [13] P. Sosík, Solving a PSPACE -complete problem by P systems with active membranes, In: M. Cavaliere, C. Martín-Vide, Gh. Păun (Eds.), Proceedings of the Brainstorming Week on Membrane Computing. Report GRLMC 26/03, 2003, pp. 305–312. Corresponding author. Department of Control Science and Engineering Huazhong University of Science and Technology Luoyu Road 1037. Fax: +86 27 87543130. Copyright © 2005 Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.